title: NewsBreak: Tesla Could Deliver 100K Vehicles – Report

NewsBreak: Tesla Could Deliver 100K Vehicles – Report

Stock Markets 2 hours ago (Sep 26, 2019 02:55PM ET)

© Reuters. Investing.com - Tesla (NASDAQ: ) CEO Elon Musk said the company could deliver 100,000 vehicles in the quarter, according to a published report. - “We have a shot at achieving our first 100,000 vehicle delivery quarter, which is an incredibly exciting milestone for our company!” Musk said in a company e-mail, Electrek reported. - The automaker is looking at net orders “tracking to reach about 110,000” according to Musk, the report said. - Tesla (NASDAQ: ) rose 4.5% in afternoon trading.
